snippet.title: Washington's First Amber Alert
snippet.description:
Sofia Lucerno Juarez disappeared years ago and has never been found. Many people have heard of her case because she was the first child for whom an Amber Alert was issued in the state of Washington. However, far fewer people have heard of the decades-old cold case of Roland Jack Spencer III, who vanished without a trace and has hardly been talked about since. Today, we'll explore both cases of these tragic disappearances, and the lives of these children who were taken too soon.

Sofia Lucerno Juarez: 0:00-10:38
Roland Jack Spencer III: 10:39-16:35

IF YOU HAVE INFORMATION ON SOPHIA, CALL:
1-800-THE-LOST
509-585-4208

IF YOU HAVE INFORMATION ON ROLAND, CALL:
1-800-THE-LOST case #1149796
(509)865.7765
(325)423.2458 (to set up a DNA appointment, NOT for high-priority info)

DISCLAIMER: I do not mean any disrespect in the creation of this video. All of the information presented in the video is information that I have found via a multitude of online sources, all of which are listed towards the end of the video. If I have an error in one of my videos, please contact me via my comments section or email so I can pin a comment on my video with corrections. If you are related to somebody discussed in the case and want this video to be taken down, please email me with your concerns. All media used is royalty-free.
